[node name="HelpText" type="Label" parent="HelpDialog/MarginContainer/VBoxContainer"]
layout_mode = 2
text = "How to Play:\n- Use Arrow keys or WASD to move.\n- Press Space to interact with NPCs and shopkeepers.\n- Buy weapons or potions from Mira. She accepts gold coins found in the world.\n- When you ask to buy an item, the merchant will tell you the cost and offer choices.\n- If you choose to buy, your gold is deducted and the item is added to your inventory.\n- Press I to open your inventory and inspect your items.\n- Talk to each character to learn more and progress quests.\n\nAbout the Game:\n- Kingdom Frontier is a story-driven RPG with market, gate, forest, and shadow tavern scenes.\n- Each NPC plays a role in the story and follows a storyline path tied to your choices.\n- Returning to the same NPC changes their dialogue based on your previous visits and relationships.\n\nNPC Roles:\n- Mira: Merchant at the Market Square. Buys and sells weapons, potions, and supplies. She remembers returning customers and adapts her offers.\n- Captain Aldric: Castle Gate guard. He allows entry to the keep when you have the right item and tests your courage.\n- Elder Thorn: Forest elder with secrets and quests. She shares ancient lore and only trusts certain heroes.\n- Shade: Shadow Guild agent offering covert missions and loyalty tests.\n\nUnity Compatibility:\n- Yes, this game can integrate with Unity. The backend API is HTTP-based, so Unity can call the same endpoints with C#.\n- In Unity, create UI panels for dialogue, options, and inventory. Use a simple C# script to send JSON requests to http://127.0.0.1:8000/get_response.\n- Parse the JSON response, show NPC text, display the 4 option buttons, and update gold/inventory locally.\n- This is beginner-friendly: start with a TextMeshPro text box, 4 UI Buttons, and UnityWebRequest for network calls.\n\nGold Tips:\n- Find gold hidden around the map and in chests.\n- Buy useful gear before tough fights."

